{
  "prob_desc_input_spec": "The first line contains a single integer $$$n$$$ — the number of Vasya's grades ($$$1 \\leq n \\leq 100$$$). The second line contains $$$n$$$ integers from $$$2$$$ to $$$5$$$ — Vasya's grades for his lab works.",
  "prob_desc_notes": "NoteIn the first sample, it is enough to redo two lab works to make two $$$4$$$s into $$$5$$$s.In the second sample, Vasya's average is already $$$4.75$$$ so he doesn't have to redo anything to get a $$$5$$$.In the second sample Vasya has to redo one lab work to get rid of one of the $$$3$$$s, that will make the average exactly $$$4.5$$$ so the final grade would be $$$5$$$.",
